From: Build Fix <fix@proton-arm.local>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 19:12:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix GStreamer API compatibility: Replace GstBufferMapInfo with GstMapInfo

GStreamer no longer exports GstBufferMapInfo in recent versions.
Replace with GstMapInfo which is the correct type for buffer mapping operations.

This resolves compilation errors:
- error: unknown type name 'GstBufferMapInfo'; did you mean 'GstMapInfo'?
- error: request for member 'data' in something not a structure or union
- error: request for member 'size' in something not a structure or union

---
 dlls/winegstreamer/media-converter/videoconv.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winegstreamer/media-converter/videoconv.c b/dlls/winegstreamer/media-converter/videoconv.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/dlls/winegstreamer/media-converter/videoconv.c
+++ b/dlls/winegstreamer/media-converter/videoconv.c
@@ -983,7 +983,7 @@ static GstFlowReturn video_conv_sink_chain(GstPad *pad, GstObject *parent, GstBu
     if (!(transcoded = gst_buffer_new_and_alloc(downstream_end - downstream_offset)))
         return GST_FLOW_ERROR;
     else
     {
-        GstBufferMapInfo map;
+        GstMapInfo map;
         size_t fill_size = 0;
 
         if (gst_buffer_map(transcoded, &map, GST_MAP_READWRITE))
